< Review>
Favorite Mexican eatery period and pretty excited to finally be able to eat inside again. Reasonable prices, generous portions and the most outstanding feature: everything is homemade there in the restaurant from the chorizo to the corn tortillas and heavenly horchata. You can taste the quality! Taco connoisseurs must visit Don Zarape #2 for what I guarantee will be some of the best tacos you'll ever eat. Space between alternating tables to encourage social distancing and if you order to go, please wait outside where seating is also available.< /Review>

<Review>Hungover?
Need Pozole or Menudo? Is it Saturday or Sunday? This place has it all. My friend and I needed Pozole ASAP after friday nights craziness. It hit the spot, delicious.
If you don't like the pigs foot I suggest you tell the lady. They don't put a bunch of maiz and theres plenty of meat.
House made torillas and they have the classic huge grill, grilling chicken outside. You can smell it a couple blocks down.
The only downside about this place is, THEY TAKE FOREVER! buttttt it's worth it in the end.
Service: The ladies are very nice and attentive.
Ambiance: Classic mexican restaurant decor with TVs</Review>< Pictures>

None< /Response>
<review>This is a  little Mexican food place that has been in this area for years and years. They also have a second location. This is the one I go to the most. This place is... Okay.  The food is pretty traditional. It's very straight to the point Mexican fare. Which is not at all a bad thing. The issue I have here is the consistency of the food. It sometimes is outstanding, it sometimes isn't. I guess you can say that about tons of restaurants though... The prices are also a bit steep.  However! They do have a fantastic perk. They have a enormous barbecue in which they use to grill chickens. SO. MANY. CHICKENS. And those are really good. I go there to eat the chicken. Just the chicken. That to me, is the only consistently good thing about this place. Order yourself a half or a whole chicken, get a cup of their nice spicy salsa, grab a Coke, and you're set. You don't need anything else.< /review></record>

< Review>
I so wanted to give 5 stars for the excellent service and troubleshooting I got from the general manager of the store for the old computer my husband desperately needed.

She was wonderful! And the purchase of our new computer came in right on time to our front door.

But when I had technical support transfer his photos to the new computer it all seemed to go well but I had difficulty picking it up because the tech was busy in the copy department. I waited for a very long time only to find that the computer was acting up. So I left for 45 minutes then came back, and waited another 25 minutes to have someone released the computer to me.

Ironically, the manager wasn't there that day and it didn't go as smooth as previously. But I highly recommend Office Max for their tech support and care for the needs of their customer.</Review>

< Review>
I work in the office of a local charter school. We needed a competent company to print and bind 15 copies of our WASC Self Study- a 170 page mix of color and b&w pages. Every person who assisted us with this went out of their way to guarantee the quality of our final product. <Name>Maria Lainez</Name><date>1615619088357< /date><rating>4<//rating>< review>
We found this place by accident. My sister and I called to ask how long the wait time was and they said 30 minutes. We were seated as soon  as we arrived. The service was phenomenal! The place is a bit tiny but perfect to spend a nice dinner date at. They have two prices, the silver $25 and the gold (forgot the price) for all you can eat. The only issue we had was my sister found a hair in her rice. The staff was quick and apologized. The experience was wonderful,  if you ever find yourself in that area please visit!</review>

< userid>
103707591633272033722</userid>
<name>Melanie Tam<//name>< Date>
1518760940757<//Date>
< Rate>
2< /Rate>
< text>
After a few attempts at other Korean BBQ restaurants on a Saturday night at 8, Yang San Bak was the only one that didn't require a wait. I guess that couldn't have been a good sign.

Three hangry friends and I went with the Combo C (for 3-4 people). For $64.99, you get brisket, rib belly, marinated beef, steak, and a bottle of soju. Between this and all of the banchan dishes, we were stuffed. It was more than enough food. The flavor of the meats and the side dishes were good overall, but some of the cuts were a bit chewy.

Service was lacking. I'm not sure if it's a Yang San Bak thing, or an LA KBBQ thing, but in NYC KBBQ spots, they help you cut up the meats, grill them, switch out your grill plate, and refill your banchan dishes. None of that happened here. We were left to handle our own meats, like peasants. And sadly, our empty banchan dishes went unfilled (waiters were nowhere to be found). I looked over at the couple next to us, and their grill was completely burnt, so it wasn't just our table.

I think next time, I'll get a snack to hold me over and wait it out at the better KBBQ restaurants.</text>

Nicholas Monter</user_name>
<pictures>None< /pictures><Resp>None<//Resp><user>101026421205983532299< /user><date>1572748743800< /date><Text>The Place: It's located in a typical LA plaza with tiny parking and random stores and restaurants. However, what isn't typical, is the fact the place itself is fairly quiet. Club music isn't blaring at 96db. You can ACTUALLY talk to the person across the table in a normal voice. If you, or someone you know has a hearing aid and love KBBQ, please go to Yang San Bak.

The Food: High quality meats and delicious sides. So let's be honest, it doesn't have the best meat, but it does have great meat at a great price. It also has one of dipping sauces ever. Seriously, that red chili sauce is amazing.

The Price: This has one of the best quality to price ratios for a KBBQ place in Koreatown. And their combo/meal includes an alcoholic drink. So this makes the place even more reasonable if you drink but hate having to pay $12 for a bottle of soju.

What I Would Change: So this place isn't as hip or trendy as the other places in KTown. But this has become one of the best overall KBBQ places to go. It isn't as busy or packed as other KBBQ places in the area. It does make me worry if they're making enough business (given the rising rents). But then again, I like that we can go at 7PM and not have to wait until 8PM to finally be seated. So maybe I don't want anything to change about this place.<//Text></record></dataset><record>

<userid>116646218087790883950< /userid><user_name>Jimmy T</user_name>< date>
1458776306941</date>
<Rate>4</Rate><review>Good quality food with decent pricing. The service is very Asian, speak up if you want anything or else you'll be ignored. We ordered a 2-3 person set, brisket, pork belly, rib fingers and bulgogi. It comes with an alcoholic drink, soju or beer. You also get a steamed egg a person and a variety of ban chans. It was a good thing I read a few reviews before going and ordered rice. You can get the rice and pour if into the moat of kimchee and make fried rice with it. The grill is a bit small so be prepared to wait a bit. Overall, I enjoyed it and will go back in the future. There wasn't a wait like some of the newer, more hip kbbq places.< /review>< Pictures>

<user_id>110898607491343797219< /user_id><Name>Klaus Dahl< /Name><Date>1621895045463<//Date>< rating>
1</rating>
< text>
5/24/21

I called Wizard Plumbing to clear a poorly draining bathroom sink, and as a precaution run the rotor rooter through the sewer pipe.  The person who answered the phone refused to give a quote.  A plumber came, cleared the sink drain and ran the rotor rooter through the sewer pipe.  He spent about 45 min on the job and charged $ 575.  He would not give me an invoice but promised one by email.  None came.  I called Wizard and again requested an invoice.  None came.

The $ 575 charge for 45 min on the job was outrageous.  Failure to send an invoice is an unacceptable business practice.

Beware!

Caveat Emptor

Klaus</text>

< review>
I recently had occasion to call Wizard Plumbing and Drain for a blocked sewer line between my garage and the street.

Although it was late at night, Franco was at my house within half an hour of my call. He had actually been about to go to bed, but he got up, got dressed, and came right over.

The service he provided was professional, courteous and fast. I was particularly  impressed by the care he took to avoid bumping into our furnishings or scratching our floor as he maneuvered his equipment through our house. Franco not only fixed the problem, he was able to show me the cause of the blockage (tree roots) by running a TV camera through our pipes to the street. I highly recommend Wizard Plumbing and Drain and especially Franco and I  would not hesitate to call them again.</review>

< Text>
We have had Wizard out twice in the last two days. The first time was for a shower back up that was coming from a plug in the main line (roots, argh). We had received an estimate from Roto-Rooter for $700; thankfully, Mark was able to fix the problem in short order for $189.

Unfortunately, the flow back had caused another clog somewhere higher up the line, causing a leak when we run water on the other side of the house. I was able to loosen this myself with a 25' auger (thinking I had fixed the problem). In the process of accessing the drain, however I bumped an attachment to the sink which began to leak and was extremely difficult to access. Mark came back, and fixed the problem at absolutely zero cost, even though he had driven out, provided his expert opinion, and spent close to half an hour tightening it up.<//Text>

love this place. All the staff is super friendly and have wonderful pleasant personalities. They treat you like you matter.
